# Clars.ai UI / UX (Impeccable-aligned)

When building or changing **UI** (pages, components, layout, motion, copy):

1. **Read project context first** — Root `.impeccable.md` (`## Design Context`). If it is empty or outdated for the task, run the **teach-impeccable** skill (`/teach-impeccable`) before large design passes.

2. **Use the bundled skills** — `.cursor/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md` plus its `reference/*.md` files (typography, color-and-contrast, spatial-design, motion-design, interaction-design, responsive-design, ux-writing). For focused passes, use command skills in the same folder: `audit`, `critique`, `normalize`, `polish`, `typeset`, `arrange`, `colorize`, etc.

3. **Stay distinctive** — Pick an intentional direction (minimal, editorial, utilitarian, etc.) and execute consistently. Avoid generic “AI template” output: overused fonts (Inter, Roboto, system-default stacks), purple/blue gradient heroes, nested card stacks, gray text on colored panels, bounce easing, decorative glass/blur everywhere.

4. **Match the stack** — Tailwind, shadcn/ui, CSS variables for theme tokens, `next/font` for fonts. New dashboard-style sections should align with **`SectionCard` / `SectionHeader`** from `src/app/dashboard/analytics/_components/analytics-page-shell.tsx` unless a screen truly needs a different pattern.

5. **Locales** — Product targets EN / FR / AR with RTL for Arabic (`cursorrules`). Prefer logical properties and `rtl:` utilities where layout mirrors.

**Attribution:** Frontend-design skill and references derive from [Impeccable](https://github.com/pbakaus/impeccable) (extends Anthropic’s frontend-design skill; Apache-2.0).
